Beijing Newspaper Highlights -- China's armed forces have made great
achievements in their modernization efforts. Now, special forces
account for more than 70 percent of its ground forces. "China Daily" --
Local governments have been urged by the State Flood-Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters to be prepared for serious floods and
drought. The Changchun-Dalian railway line in northeast China has been
brought to a standstill by floods. -- No major breakthrough was made in
a new round of informal talks on China's accession to the World Trade
Organization, which ended last Friday. Long Yongtu, China's chief
negotiator, sharply criticized the United States for blocking the
negotiations, especially on the drafting of key items of China's
accession protocol. -- The remains of a sacrificial shrine dedicated to
Qin Shi Huang, the first emperor of the Qin Dynasty (221-207 BC), have
been unearthed in the emperor's mausoleum in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
